Vice President Pence visited Arizona and expressed the federal government's support for the state during the COVID-19 pandemic. He commended Governor Ducey for his leadership and efforts to slow the spread of the virus. Pence brought with him Dr. Deborah Birx and other officials to assist with testing, personal protective equipment, and healthcare resources. Governor Ducey thanked the federal administration for their support and emphasized the importance of following safety measures such as wearing masks, practicing physical distancing, and washing hands. Arizona implemented measures to pause certain activities, including gyms, bars, waterpark tubing, movie theaters, and large public gatherings for the next 30 days. The governor urged residents to celebrate Independence Day responsibly and emphasized the need for personal responsibility to overcome the challenges faced in July.